# Infrastructure & Tooling
- Use Angular 13 with Angular Material 13 as the core framework.
- Use Angular CLI v13.x for project generation and serving.
- Use npm as the package manager.

## CLI
- Prefer Angular CLI (`ng`) commands for generation, serving, building, and testing.
- Run all commands in non-interactive mode where possible.

## Package Management
- Use `npm` as the package manager; never install global packages.
- Use only `~` for package versions in `package.json` (e.g., `"@angular/core": "~13.0.0"`). Never use `^` or `*`.
- All dependencies must be installed in the repository root.

## Project Structure
- This is a single Angular application (not a monorepo).
- The project root is `/Users/yizhaq.baroz/IdeaProjects/angular-13-playground`.
- Specs and docs live under `specs/` in the project root.
